[{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"# `LET` statement\r\nThe `LET` statement sets and stores a value which can then be used in a subsequent query. A parameter can store any value, including the result of a query."},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"## Statement syntax\r\n\r\n```surrealql\r\nLET $@parameter = @value;\r\n```"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"## Example usage\r\n\r\nThe following query shows example usage of this statement."},{"kind":2,"language":"surrealql","value":"-- Define the parameter\r\nLET $name = \"tobie\";\r\n-- Use the parameter\r\nCREATE person SET name = $name;"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"The following query shows the `LET` statement being used to store the result of a subquery."},{"kind":2,"language":"surrealql","value":"-- Define the parameter\r\nLET $adults = (SELECT * FROM person WHERE age > 18);\r\n-- Use the parameter\r\nUPDATE $adults SET adult = true;"}]